org.openbel.framework.compiler
Interface DefaultPhaseTwo

All Known Implementing Classes:
PhaseTwoImpl
public interface DefaultPhaseTwo

BEL compiler phase two interface.

Phase two compilation consists of:

  1. Stage 1 -- Merge Proto Networks
    Merge each Document's Phase I ProtoNetwork representation.
  2. Stage 2 -- Load Namespace Equivalences
    Load namespace equivalence indices.
  3. Stage 3 -- Equivalence Merged Proto Network
    Equivalence the Phase II / Stage 1 merged ProtoNetwork. This stage only needs to execute if the user provided namespace equivalences in Stage 2.
  4. Stage 4 -- Externalize the Merged/Equivalenced Proto Network
    Externalize the merged/equivalenced ProtoNetwork.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>
